Hermes Investment Management Ltd Raises Its Position in China Biologic Products, Inc. (CBPO) 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsHermes Investment Management Ltd Raises Its Position in China Biologic Products, Inc. (CBPO)
July 21, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



China Biologic Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:CBPO). 
 Hermes Investment Management Ltd reports that it bought 19,893 shares in quarter ending 06/30/2017 increasing its holdings in China Biologic Products, Inc.  by 3.2%.  Its position was worth $73,641,000 an increase of $10,437,000 as of quarter end. 
 Other firms have also shifted positions in (CBPO).   As of quarter end Manning & Napier Advisors LLC had sold  a total of 38,550 shares trimming its stake by 71.7%. The value of the investment in China Biologic Products, Inc. decreased from $5,385,000 to $1,723,000 a change of $3,662,000 for the reporting period. As of the end of the quarter Vontobel Asset Management Inc had disposed of 6,439 shares trimming its position 11.2%. The value of the company’s investment in China Biologic Products, Inc. went from $5,735,000 to $5,750,000 a change of 0.3% quarter over quarter.
 Clinton Group Inc downsized its holdings by shedding 9,964 shares a decrease of 82.7% in the quarter. Clinton Group Inc now controls 2,089 shares with a value of $209,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 83.9%.
  On March 1 the stock rating was downgraded to “Neutral” from “Outperform” in a report issued by Credit Suisse. On February 29 Jefferies held the company rating at “Buy” but moved down the price target from $138.00 to $136.00.        Advertisement






 August 7 investment analysts at Jefferies maintained a company rating of “Buy” but raised the price expectation  to $146.00 from $122.00. Bank of America starting coverage on the stock giving it an initial rating of “Buy” and setting a price target of $135.00.
 November 6 investment analysts at Jefferies held the stock rating at “Buy” and raised the price target from $57.00 to $76.00. On July 24 Jefferies made no change to the stock rating of “Buy” and raised the price expectation from $52.00 to $57.00.
 The company is now down since yesterday’s close of $104.29.  It is trading at $103.28 marginally under the 50 day moving average which is $108.45 and which is marginally lower than the 200 day moving average of $108.85.  The 50 day moving average went down by -4.75% and the 200 day average went down by -5.10%. 
 China Biologic Products, Inc.’s P/E ratio is 26.75 and the market cap is 2.81B.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $3.86 and is estimated to be $5.05 for the current year with 27,201,000 shares now outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $1.24 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $5.81. 
 Investors are a little more bullish on shares of China Biologic Products, Inc. if you watch the change in short interest.  The stock experienced a fall in short interest between June 15, 2017 and May 31, 2017 of -31.73%.  Short interest fell 514,438 over that timeframe.  The short-interest ratio decreased to 6.8 and the percentage of shorted shares was 0.04% on May 31.
