Hermes Investment Management Appoints Orla Murphy as Research Director
May 30 17
Hermes Investment Management has hired a new research director to manage MiFID II issues. Orla Murphy will be responsible for establishing, reporting and linking research value, managing the research budget and transaction cost analysis, along with a host of other regulatory issues surrounding the new MiFID II regulations. In her new role, Murphy will report to Hermesâ  head of investment Eoin Murray, and will also oversee the procurement of equity and credit research from brokers and independent research providers for Hermes investment teams. Murphy joins the firm from VTB Capital, where her roles included business manager for international equities and cross-asset business manager.  Prior to this, Murphy also held roles at Barclays Wealth and Fidelity Investments.


